MediaWorkflow create and update are synchronous
reread flows. OCI returns the body immediately
and the resource exposes only ACTIVE,
NEEDS_ATTENTION, and DELETED, so the reviewed
runtime does not publish provisioning or
updating lifecycle buckets.
The published runtime treats NEEDS_ATTENTION as
terminal failure without requeue and does not
invent service-local work-request polling.
Pre-create reuse scopes by compartmentId and
uses the SDK displayName filter when
spec.displayName is present. Adoption requires a
unique exact match on the reviewed identity
surface.
Delete confirmation treats either a DELETED
lifecycle response or a NotFound reread as
terminal and otherwise keeps the finalizer until
OCI stops returning the resource.
Matching create-time locks are normalized out of
steady-state parity by ignoring OCI-populated
timeCreated metadata, but changing requested
locks after create remains out of scope.
end note
